05852nam a22007935i 9783110603064DE-B159720210621102733.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210621t20192019gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2019947917  a97831106030647 a10.1515/97831106030642doi  a(DE-B1597)495207  a(OCoLC)1121054960  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aHIS0020002bisacsh0481ua590.9qDE-101223/ger00aAnimal Kingdom of Heaven :bAnthropozoological Aspects in the Late Antique World /ced. by Ingo Schaaf. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2019] 4c©2019  a1 online resource (V, 161 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aMillennium-Studien / Millennium Studies ;v8000tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAnimal Kingdom of Heaven. Anthropozoological Aspects in the Late Antique World -- t«Ecco, io vi mando come agnelli in mezzo ai lupi» (Mt 10,16): eretici e animali nel cristianesimo antico -- tThe Function of Dragon Episodes in Early Hagiography -- tTiere in symbolischer Deutung: Der Physiologus -- tGregorio Magno e il mondo animale, tra curiositas e simbologia -- tThe Flight of the Phoenix to Paradise in Ancient Literature and Iconography -- tDas Tier, der Mensch und Gott in Laktanzens De opificio Dei -- tIndex rerum et nominum -- tIndex locorum0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aThe essays collected in this volume apply an interdisciplinary approach to explore aspects of the relationship between animal and human in late antiquity. With a focus on ways that anthropozoological connections were defined in the emergent Christian religious discourse of the epoch, the authors contribute to our understanding of a thematic area largely neglected in previous research.  aZu den Forschungstrends der jüngeren Vergangenheit zählt ohne Zweifel die kulturwissenschaftliche Untersuchung von Tier-Mensch-Beziehungen, doch werden Ansätze aus den Human-Animal Studies (HAS) in den Altertumswissenschaften - und hier insbesondere für den Bereich der sogenannten "Spätantike" - vergleichsweise selten fruchtbar gemacht. Aus philologisch-historischer Perspektive helfen die Beiträge des vorliegenden Bandes dabei, diese zu diagnostizierende Unausgewogenheit der chronologischen Fokussierung zu überwinden. Von den ersten Jahrhunderten bis zur Schwelle des Mittelalters bietet der Band Einblicke in das komplexe Verhältnis von Tier und Mensch und geht dabei der facettenreichen Frage nach, wo und auf welche Weise anthropozoologische Aspekte in der zunehmend christlich werdenden spätantiken Welt zum Gegenstand der Reflexion werden konnten.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aAntike. 4aTier-Mensch-Beziehung. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aHuman-animal relationship.1 aBrasi, Diego De, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranchi, Roberta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLecocq, Françoise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoreschini, Claudio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOgden, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchaaf, Ingo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchaaf, Ingo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchneider, Horst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gru